      • combineWith

        @Nonnull
NonLiteralPath combineWith​(@Nonnull
                           FhirPath target,
                           @Nonnull
                           Dataset<Row> dataset,
                           @Nonnull
                           String expression,
                           @Nonnull
                           Column idColumn,
                           @Nonnull
                           Optional<Column> eidColumn,
                           @Nonnull
                           Column valueColumn,
                           boolean singular,
                           @Nonnull
                           Optional<Column> thisColumn)
        Creates a path that can be used to represent a collection which includes elements from both a source and a target path.
        Parameters:
        target - the path the merge the invoking path with
        dataset - the Dataset that can be used to evaluate this path against data
        expression - the FHIRPath expression that represents the result
        idColumn - a Column within the dataset containing the identity of the subject resource
        eidColumn - a Column that represents the unique ID for an element within a collection
        valueColumn - a Column within the dataset containing the values of the nodes
        singular - an indicator of whether this path represents a single-valued collection
        thisColumn - for paths that traverse from the $this keyword, this column refers to the values in the collection
        Returns:
        the resulting new NonLiteralPath
